@italiano40 PHP C++ hybrid code? Stupid and dumbass. Plz read http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HipHop_for_PHP. And where did you find that google uses php? Save your dumb words for yourself. CI, Kohana, CakePHP, Rails and Django are both WEB FRAMEWORKS, asshole. They both are suposed to do the same thing: help the user to build whatever they want faster(and secure) than building from scratch. Your atrophied brain does not let you think?
---
I'm so sorry to change the subject of the thread. CI is a great framework, I still use it in my projects. Its documentation is the best I ever found. Framework is a personal thing. You use what you like. I'm using Kohana and FuelPHP too, both awesome, but i don't think you can just say one is better than other.
